# DEVLOG.md: both devs add a changelog-table row at the same anchor on every
# push — a guaranteed textual conflict with zero semantic conflict. The
# built-in union driver keeps BOTH sides' lines instead of stopping the
# rebase. Caveat: if two pushes rewrite the SAME paragraph (e.g. "Current
# focus"), union concatenates both versions silently — eyeball that section
# after a merge/rebase that touched DEVLOG.
DEVLOG.md merge=union
